 2010: NA)","Welsh: from the personal name <i>Ithell</i>, Middle Welsh <i>Ithael</i>. See   Bethel  ."]},{"name":"Bethea","meanings":["Possibly an altered form of Welsh   Bethel  .","History: The name was brought to VA by John Bethea (known as ‘English John’) (1684– after 1750), who settled in Nansemond, VA."]},{"name":"Bethell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]}]},{"name":"Aelis","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Alice","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."]},{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aelis Rethel was born in 1010, her father, Manasses de Rethel, was 60 and her mother, Dada, was 41. She had at least 1 son with Rainald Château-Du-Loir."},"et":{"1010–":"1010–Surnud","1010–Female":"1010–Surnud","1022–1080":"1022–1080","1010–1065":"1010–1065","1040–1087":"1040–1087","0950–1048":"0950–1048","0970–1033":"0970–1033","1080":"1080","0950":"0950","0970":"0970","1048":"1048","1033":"1033","1022":"1022","1010":"1010","1087":"1087","1065":"1065","1040":"1040","Château-Porcien, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Château-Porcien, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1010–":"1010–Kuollut","1010–Female":"1010–Kuollut","1022–1080":"1022–1080","1010–1065":"1010–1065","1040–1087":"1040–1087","0950–1048":"0950–1048","0970–1